snippet: Edvald Boasson Hagen of Norway led a sprint finish to win the third stage of the Critérium du Dauphiné, while Bradley Wiggins of Britain retained the overall lead.
abstract: Norwegian cyclist Edvald Boasson Hagen wins the third stage of the Criterium du Dauphine bicycle race, while Bradley Wiggins of Britain retains the overall lead.
lead_paragraph: Edvald Boasson Hagen of Norway led a sprint finish to win the third stage of the Critérium du Dauphiné, while Bradley Wiggins of Britain retained the overall lead.
